<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-labs-readme" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>About Labs</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Scriber Labs documents projects that link directly to repositories. Each project
      should have a clear README, overview, design notes, and postmortem.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-lab-structure">
    <title>Project Structure</title>
    <p>Each project directory should contain:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><p><term>README.ptx:</term> Repository link and project scope</p></li>
      <li><p><term>overview.ptx:</term> High-level explanation of the project</p></li>
      <li><p><term>design-notes.ptx:</term> Architectural decisions</p></li>
      <li><p><term>postmortem.ptx:</term> Lessons and reflections</p></li>
    </ul>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-lab-guidelines">
    <title>Guidelines</title>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Link to the actual repository early and often</p></li>
      <li><p>Keep scope clear: what is this project about?</p></li>
      <li><p>Document decisions, not just implementations</p></li>
      <li><p>Write postmortems regardless of success or failure</p></li>
      <li><p>Cross-reference to Scribing where relevant</p></li>
    </ul>
  </subsection>

</section>
